Boil a half-full #kettle{}.

Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat. Add the 
@Basmati Rice{150%grams} and cook for ~{10-12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and pop back in the pan. Cover with a #lid{} and 
leave to the side until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, heat a large #frying pan{} on high heat (no oil).

Once hot, add the @Diced Chorizo{90%grams} and @British Beef Mince{240%grams} and fry 
until browned, ~{4-5%minutes}. Use a #spoon{} to break it up as it cooks, then drain 
and discard any excess fat.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Meanwhile, halve the @Bell Pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin 
strips.

Drain and rinse the @Black Beans{1%carton} in a sieve.

Add the sliced pepper to the mince, then stir and cook for ~{2%minutes}.

Stir in the @Mexican Style Spice Mix{1%sachet}, @Finely Chopped Tomatoes{1%carton} and 
@Beef Stock Paste{10%grams}.

Add the black beans and @Water for the Sauce{150%milliliters} and bring to the boil.

Lower the heat to medium and simmer, stirring occasionally, until the sauce has 
thickened, ~{8-10%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, grate the @Mature Cheddar Cheese{30%grams}.

Once cooked, taste and season the chilli with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed.

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{}, then share between your #bowls{}.

Spoon the chilli on top, then finish with a sprinkle of cheese.

Enjoy!